  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In 2018, 10 detention centers in France will start organisational programs to improve the
      quality of screening of oral diseases, relatively to French recommendations, among new
      prisoners in France. Our study aims 1) to assess the prevalence and nosology of oral diseases
      ; 2) to describe the care pathway of participants during their stay in the detention center
      where they were included ; 3) to assess the cost of care per patient, from a societal
      perspective, using a top-down method.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
